Package: dsVertClient
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Client Functions for Vertically Partitioned Data
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Sarrat González", email = "david.sarrat@isglobal.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Miron", "Banjac", email = "miron.banjac@isglobal.org",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Juan R", "González", email = "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org",
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: Client-side DataSHIELD functions for privacy-preserving analysis
    of vertically partitioned federated data. Provides record alignment, GLM,
    Cox PH, negative binomial, multinomial, ordinal, LMM, GEE, GLMM, IPW,
    multiple imputation, LASSO, contingency, correlation, PCA, and descriptive
    workflows over the companion dsVert server package. Exported routes use the
    non-disclosive product surface; disclosive or materially suboptimal
    historical routes have been removed from the user API.
